[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Java file writes**\n\nI’m wondering if there’s an issue with how List.of writes newlines. When using Files.write in Java, it appears that each line might include a newline, but the RuntimeInstance test is expecting no trailing newline. They used List.of(\"#foreach...\"), but the template didn’t produce a newline. It seems Files.write includes line separators, and I need to double-check the JDK documentation. It typically appends after each line, but I’m curious about how the existing tests passed. Maybe the JDK implementation doesn’t add a newline after the last line?\n\n**Assessing singleton and resource loading**\n\nI’m considering whether Generator.getInstance() properly returns a singleton before initializing the velocityEngine, with parse filling in the default properties. I'm concerned because the default properties context includes PropertiesUtil, which uses ClassUtils.getNewInstance for dynamic access. While it can cover additional dynamic access, should I focus only on the active class? The existing ClassUtilsTest already handles getNewInstance, but metadata for new classes like FileUtil might be an issue. I could simply assert that the generator is non-null and its methods work without broadening dynamic reflection. However, I want to ensure that resources are loaded adequately. Should I use getTemplate or check output paths? Reading properties through parse might be the way forward.\n\n**Reviewing resource properties and dynamic access**\n\nI’m thinking that the resource properties are only visible through fillContextProperties using reflection, which adds dynamic access beyond the active class. This could be alright since they come from the active class’s default properties behavior. I wonder if I could call context.get, but there aren’t any direct properties. I could also try invoking setOutputPath, but that doesn’t seem viable either. Another idea is to use generator.parse with the template referencing `$strings.removeAndHump(\"foo_bar\")` to assert the output, though that involves the same reflection. I need to keep in mind the dynamic-access rules to avoid tests for unrelated classes.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_019ff140196a9aeb016a032f23e89c81a0a1edf7ae29f47690\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqAy8xSWDW60NE7Q29WD1YsscFnu2Hgh-zhrLctEbiZmPaRFWJgyZxDhZJdN1l7Hit49CplOCGIMdvWjB1g-G3NgcAQjBuRLR9MjLbK4z4QovYa9F6GO1_NWFeVd0l4sYJ_UpY9aIdtaYH0eRlduHvAyAv-heXihQ78yS_I5zrolJSnMHynEKgCODfVFNVPn4ZnxNrWa_1cBqRQtB6-YJv4w-EK8MWdeLdrCoZra24mozgV8a8cOY6WjUsmkxO7YD5kpNNG8sqDGr9zGl2AN9KlsOa3DwC0pB4pP1S4tXWVGEP7JjCTxvS_0ZJRGDV0Rojg29KUXQ2HHdNhep4sT5KRrMcCNlVkpv8X1MJopX5I7M2f_iyocuc8xFGHigVVgMYz-a_BYhM6qTuz58v2eMxjhdVCsCcijHSHjhoH0807cTjso_amhyvIiLXl7yoVZLG8AiuR9OCz76j3XztLls7SEOMyPMYgPR-D3wVQA9hwSiXCd4QdtYzLzxYs3gusoMlbFOs_JHuku0jCYG6b2679KCVht70WYabhPtIacaclrcPbA9lH4RXlKCU4VYOCOI8c2KeVbgYWaUk9IJ9SMNH8DWEpY-Fa-8KviWi8C5YIpn07sTGmKL67KOpQ5YT8ELHRmZhCByB0WN35AtBayWIC27hqN1cd8TJkB6YNZLEDaJSKTwBO2W_ZgraiVoPt8A2VJrVsBaHxGdeyArLaeOG8EN9AOwjPt5lVCuztaX2D3vA9UjS-PbHtoHINVCY0fWPCoyJChcR3iFYz_8Ode8YcRBU8I7Me1NhbJDUxIzmpZfbscDo__fThng6TpXGkmpBeu0pMijZoOkYDElE2ZUGgLDI_76Uxoib5DsZPYTy4LIZufFuuWIfdquQuejBw7V5SXrlvO-C0AeWU2BdO-39ZY8ogEZ4pi7CdEZ2jZlljemckdEhWiUkuALdm_YDUTbxf2g66ir8wEp5DNFPB4U2wM3sWBlTwnooBxnnkSnwHTmZVXUEXJjiMWBO51efqffTF6IWvH8rgs7i3fgjXd2DJJlX8JHd1aFo2OSq_RHZKV-vWJYvSdoh0dB0vCDfHkcJn0klFkdMUilMKwc7F3FjRz4nGK_U0lNGjKSVliCRMDq30qd7_27S5SPPujJnFjw6Yq8HZ7OFHbM5fuuk83kjvwNPKqDUmTwKIEb43ZvhXfghexKnuVH5fCvDdV0GTVS9I25fpaURMOrrKG938y3xOQLgsAHnbGLbLI1ATykfkcueRLnPHqyjFo9T7SiR0GoNjrjd8cCJ7BJnoUmJHqKQEQvahJLP3WVpf25rpKY-NVWXVzY94Bd-nLrrb0wivLEgAtpO1MgbGvKenpT5U34VnRZBghM0q-qK7aEluUnvMbOkKRbY_CY6xBdB-IJBKBXOTjDWfl0H6lxVSXRPakRmuZGaysScflUok6A5P2tjiKMr6tlHZJeRrm4nQr_EswHyN544vruxgvQBi5cawu7Xo8oEtBtgWYwSwVEbhL9dyo5hGValv4FHuoj8oWZ2fGycjPwtX0rgTFG8pGDNy9yP00CsKcJlgpMYapoYy-EWJsHGBP9i-7s5N2mxp-